#### Significance of the ```synchronize``` keyword

The ```synchronize``` method is used to synchronize access to a shared resource. This means that multiple threads can access the same resource at the same time without causing any problems.

#### When methods should be ```sychronized```

Methods should be ```synchronize``` when they access a shared resource that multiple threads can access at the same time. This ensures that only one thread can access the resource at a time, which prevents race conditions and data inconsistencies.

#### What it means programmatically and logicly

Programmatically, ```synchronize``` means that the method will be executed in a serialized manner, which means that only one thread can execute the method at a time. Logically, ```synchronize ``` means that the method will only be executed by one thread at a time, which ensures that the method will not be executed by multiple threads at the same time.

